00:01:24,290 --> 00:01:26,426
DIGIMON ARE THE CHAMPIONS

35
00:01:26,459 --> 00:01:28,461
DIGIMON --
DIGITAL MONSTERS

36
00:01:28,461 --> 00:01:30,330
DIGIMON

37
00:01:31,563 --> 00:01:34,563
[ BEEPING ]

38
00:01:34,563 --> 00:01:36,965
THERE SHE IS.
OUR ONE-WAY TICKET HOME.

39
00:01:36,965 --> 00:01:38,367
WHAT IS THAT?

40
00:01:42,930 --> 00:01:46,700
Guilmon: OH, I HOPE IT DOESN'T
BLOW OUR ARK AWAY.

41
00:01:46,734 --> 00:01:49,503
[ SCREAMING ]

42
00:01:49,537 --> 00:01:50,905
IT'S OKAY, SUZIE.

43
00:01:50,938 --> 00:01:53,374
EVERYONE HURRY UP
AND GET ON!

44
00:01:53,407 --> 00:01:56,377
[ Thinking ] JERI, COME ON,
WE GOT TO GET ON!

45
00:01:56,410 --> 00:01:58,846
GUARDROMON, A LITTLE HELP!

46
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:00,581
BUT OF COURSE.

47
00:02:00,581 --> 00:02:03,317
Henry: LET'S GO! THE ARK
COULD LEAVE ANY MINUTE!

48
00:02:03,317 --> 00:02:06,320
Takato: BUT WAIT! THERE'S
STILL NO SIGN OF RIKA!

49
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,489
Guilmon: TAKATO, GET ON!

50
00:02:08,556 --> 00:02:10,724
IN A MINUTE!
THEN I'M COMING DOWN!

51
00:02:10,758 --> 00:02:15,062
NO! YOU PROMISED DAD
YOU'D GO HOME, REMEMBER?

52
00:02:15,095 --> 00:02:17,731
HE'S MAKING YOU A BIG BATCH
OF GUILMON BREAD.

53
00:02:17,765 --> 00:02:19,567
YEAH...

54
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:22,870
[ Thinking ]
RIKA, WHERE ARE YOU?

55
00:02:24,872 --> 00:02:27,374
Renamon: IMPMON WAS RIGHT.

56
00:02:27,374 --> 00:02:29,243
WE ARE OUT OF OUR
TEENY-TINY MINDS.

57
00:02:29,276 --> 00:02:31,378
WE'LL MAKE IT.

58
00:02:31,412 --> 00:02:33,514
NOT AT THE RATE
I'M CRAWLING ALONG.

59
00:02:33,547 --> 00:02:35,849
I NEED MORE STRENGTH.

60
00:02:35,883 --> 00:02:38,384
I HAVE JUST THE PICK-ME-UP.

61
00:02:38,384 --> 00:02:39,886
ALL RIGHT!

62
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:43,556
HELLO? HEY, JERI,
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

63
00:02:43,623 --> 00:02:47,126
OH, WHY WON'T YOU SAY
ANYTHING TO ME, HUH?

64
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:48,594
YEAH, KID,
ARE YOU OKAY?

65
00:02:48,628 --> 00:02:50,363
WE'LL BE HOME SOON,
JERI.

66
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:51,597
YEAH, SOONER THAN SOON.

67
00:02:51,631 --> 00:02:53,599
[ CRASH ]

68
00:02:53,633 --> 00:02:56,803
WE'RE MOVING,
WE'RE MOVING!

69
00:02:56,836 --> 00:03:00,273
AAH! HURRY, TAKATO!

70
00:03:00,306 --> 00:03:01,702
BUT THEY'RE NOT HERE YET!

71
00:03:01,702 --> 00:03:03,704
HENRY, DON'T YOU THINK WE'D
BETTER GO LOOK FOR THEM?

72
00:03:03,704 --> 00:03:04,872
YEAH.

73
00:03:04,872 --> 00:03:07,007
NO, I'LL GET THEM.

74
00:03:07,041 --> 00:03:08,375
CYBERDRAMON?

75
00:03:08,409 --> 00:03:10,411
[ CYBERDRAMON GROWLS ]

76
00:03:10,478 --> 00:03:12,680
Ryo: WE'LL BE BACK
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT!

77
00:03:12,713 --> 00:03:14,381
BE CAREFUL!

78
00:03:14,448 --> 00:03:16,217
Kazu: RIKA IS MESSING UP
THE PROGRAM.

79
00:03:16,217 --> 00:03:18,119
THAT ISSOLIKE HER.

80
00:03:18,152 --> 00:03:19,720
OW!

81
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,830
OH, NO! TAKATO!

82
00:03:21,830 --> 00:03:23,130
HOW DO WE STOP THIS THING?

83
00:03:23,130 --> 00:03:25,165
WE GOT TO FIND
THE BRAKES!

84
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,633
ARK! COME ON, STOP!

85
00:03:26,633 --> 00:03:28,635
OR WE COULD JUST
YELL AT IT.

86
00:03:28,669 --> 00:03:30,637
ARK, PLEASE,
TAKATO'S NOT ON YET.

87
00:03:30,637 --> 00:03:32,973
WE CAN'T LEAVE.
STOP IT!

88
00:03:33,006 --> 00:03:35,776
GUILMON, YOU DO REALIZE
YOU'RE TALKING TO A BOAT.

89
00:03:35,809 --> 00:03:38,612
TAKATO, TRY AND JUMP ON.

90
00:03:38,645 --> 00:03:40,614
OKAY!

91
00:03:40,647 --> 00:03:42,816
THIS ISN'T GOOD.

92
00:03:42,816 --> 00:03:44,284
Yamaki:
THIS IS EXCELLENT.

93
00:03:44,318 --> 00:03:46,820
LOOK, THE ARK --
IT'S HEADING BACK.

94
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:48,489
MM-HMM.

95
00:03:48,489 --> 00:03:51,225
LET'S JUST HOPE THE CHILDREN
ARE ONBOARD.

96
00:03:51,258 --> 00:03:54,862
Woman: ARK TRAJECTORY CONFIRMED.
CALCULATING EMERGENCE POINT.

97
00:03:54,862 --> 00:03:57,564
THE TRACK BEAM IS STRONG
AND STABLE.

98
00:03:57,598 --> 00:03:59,733
ENERGY RESOURCE AT 60%.

99
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:02,169
IT'S WORKING!

100
00:04:02,202 --> 00:04:04,171
MY LITTLE BABY
IS COMING HOME,

101
00:04:04,204 --> 00:04:06,173
THANKS TO DECENTRALIZED
COMPUTING.

102
00:04:06,206 --> 00:04:08,642
HOT DOG! I DO BELIEVE
I AM A GENIUS!

103
00:04:08,675 --> 00:04:11,011
Man: HEY, GENIUS, YOU GOT
THE NEXT CALCULATIONS?

104
00:04:11,078 --> 00:04:12,646
PIECE OF CAKE.

105
00:04:15,148 --> 00:04:18,151
"THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
PHASE ONE SUCCESSFUL.

106
00:04:18,151 --> 00:04:20,654
NEXT, PLEASE PROCEED
WITH REMAINING CALCULATIONS."

107
00:04:20,721 --> 00:04:22,456
ALL RIGHT.

108
00:04:22,489 --> 00:04:24,458
WITH EVERYONE
ALL OVER THE WORLD HELPING,

109
00:04:24,491 --> 00:04:26,059
WE'LL GET RIKA BACK
IN NO TIME.

110
00:04:26,093 --> 00:04:28,595
OH, RIKA,
PLEASE BE ON THAT ARK.

111
00:04:35,235 --> 00:04:37,170
Henry: NO! KEEP RUNNING!

112
00:04:37,204 --> 00:04:38,705
YOU CAN DO IT!

113
00:04:38,705 --> 00:04:40,073
TAKATO!

114
00:04:40,107 --> 00:04:42,542
AAH!

115
00:04:42,542 --> 00:04:44,211
TAKATO!

116
00:04:44,211 --> 00:04:46,346
Henry: CAREFUL, GUILMON,
YOU'LL FALL!

117
00:04:46,380 --> 00:04:48,582
NOT IF I CAN HELP IT!

118
00:04:48,649 --> 00:04:51,084
MOMENTIE! WE'RE COMING!

119
00:04:51,151 --> 00:04:53,887
OH!

120
00:04:53,954 --> 00:04:56,223
AH! IT'S WORKING!

121
00:04:56,223 --> 00:04:58,625
Terriermon: GOOD THING.
MY EARS ARE CRAMPING!

122
00:04:58,659 --> 00:04:59,559
HUH?

123
00:05:02,596 --> 00:05:04,698
OH, NO!

124
00:05:04,698 --> 00:05:08,302
CALUMON!

125
00:05:08,368 --> 00:05:09,703
[ SCREAMING ]

126
00:05:09,736 --> 00:05:12,906
OH, ARK, YOU GOTTA STOP!

127
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:15,876
PLEASE LISTEN TO ME!

128
00:05:15,909 --> 00:05:17,244
STOP!

129
00:05:20,713 --> 00:05:22,043
WHAT? WHAT'S GOING ON?

130
00:05:22,043 --> 00:05:24,446
WHAT ON EARTH'S HAPPENING?
WHY DID THE ARK STOP?

131
00:05:24,446 --> 00:05:26,581
GET DOLPHIN -- NOW!

132
00:05:30,162 --> 00:05:32,205
HEY, LOOK. IT STOPPED.

133
00:05:32,205 --> 00:05:33,606
BUT WHY?

134
00:05:33,673 --> 00:05:35,341
[ YELLING ]

135
00:05:35,374 --> 00:05:37,643
Ryo: HEY, WAIT FOR US! HEY!

136
00:05:37,643 --> 00:05:41,647
HMM? IS THAT
WHO I THINK IT IS?

137
00:05:41,647 --> 00:05:44,317
LOOK WHAT THE CAT
DRAGGED IN!

138
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:46,519
RIKA! MM-HMM!

139
00:05:46,552 --> 00:05:49,288
ALL RIGHT, RIKA!
I KNEW YOU'D MAKE IT!

140
00:05:49,322 --> 00:05:50,823
[ TYPING ]

141
00:05:50,857 --> 00:05:53,192
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE,
DAISY?

142
00:05:53,259 --> 00:05:55,828
I'M NOT SURE, BUT IT SEEMS
AS IF THE ARK'S

143
00:05:55,828 --> 00:05:58,664
ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
IS SOMEHOW ACTING ON ITS OWN.

144
00:05:58,698 --> 00:06:00,833
THE ARK'S NOT RESPONDING,
DOLPHIN!

145
00:06:00,867 --> 00:06:02,835
HAS THE PROGRAM
GONE RENEGADE?

146
00:06:02,869 --> 00:06:05,738
IMPOSSIBLE. I WROTE
THAT A.I. PROGRAM MYSELF!

147
00:06:05,771 --> 00:06:08,007
THINK -- WHERE DID YOU GET
THE CODE FROM?

148
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:11,177
IF MEMORY SERVES,
FROM THE DIGIMON CORE PROGRAM!

149
00:06:15,214 --> 00:06:17,516
I USED THE SAME ARTIFICIAL LIFE
PROGRAM THAT WE USED

150
00:06:17,550 --> 00:06:20,152
TO CREATE THE DIGIMON
TO POWER THE ARK.

151
00:06:20,152 --> 00:06:22,989
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
I COULD GET THE MACHINE TO WORK.

152
00:06:23,022 --> 00:06:25,825
HERE! THIS IS IT!
BUT EVEN SO, THIS SHOULDN'T

153
00:06:25,825 --> 00:06:28,294
HAVE CAUSED THE ARK
TO THINK FOR ITSELF.

154
00:06:28,327 --> 00:06:31,197
Rika: HEY THERE.
NEED A LIFT?

155
00:06:31,264 --> 00:06:33,096
YEAH!

156
00:06:33,096 --> 00:06:35,298
GOING UP!

157
00:06:40,203 --> 00:06:42,071
WHOA!

158
00:06:42,105 --> 00:06:44,741
AAH!

159
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:48,682
WELL, MISS TARDY, WHAT DO YOU
HAVE TO SAY FOR YOURSELF?

160
00:06:48,682 --> 00:06:50,512
SORRY.

161
00:06:50,546 --> 00:06:53,849
[ Gasps ] IT'S HIM.

162
00:06:53,882 --> 00:06:56,518
RIKA, ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR
CHICKEN-FRIED MIND?

163
00:06:56,518 --> 00:06:58,520
YOU WENT BACK
TO SAVE IMPMON?

164
00:06:58,554 --> 00:06:59,821
MM-HMM.

165
00:06:59,855 --> 00:07:01,790
WELL, I'VE SAID IT BEFORE

166
00:07:01,790 --> 00:07:04,426
AND I'LL SAY IT AGAIN,
YOU'RE CRAZIER THAN CATFISH.

167
00:07:04,459 --> 00:07:06,495
[ GROANING ]

168
00:07:06,562 --> 00:07:08,630
Guardromon:
CRAZIER THAN CATFISH!

169
00:07:08,697 --> 00:07:10,299
HUH?

170
00:07:10,299 --> 00:07:12,267
HEY, COME UP
WITH YOUR OWN LINE!

171
00:07:12,301 --> 00:07:14,937
[ BUZZING ]

172
00:07:15,003 --> 00:07:17,339
UH, GUYS...

173
00:07:17,372 --> 00:07:19,541
HUH? A DIGIVICE!

174
00:07:19,575 --> 00:07:22,444
WOW! HELLO, HELLO.

175
00:07:22,511 --> 00:07:25,147
AHH...MARINEANGEMON?

176
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:28,350
I GET IT. YOU'RE MY TAMER,
I MEAN, MY PARTNER.

177
00:07:28,350 --> 00:07:30,352
AND YOU'RE A MEGA!

178
00:07:30,385 --> 00:07:34,056
THAT MAKES ME A TAMER
TO A MEGA!

179
00:07:34,122 --> 00:07:38,060
OH, I THINK I'M GOING
TO FAINT.

180
00:07:38,126 --> 00:07:41,763
Takato: AMAZING. I WONDER HOW
HE ENDED UP IN KENTA'S POCKET.

181
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:46,501
Kazu: I'M AMAZED
HE'S STILL BREATHING.

182
00:07:46,535 --> 00:07:48,270
HAVE YOU SEEN WHAT KENTA
KEEPS IN HIS POCKETS?

183
00:07:48,303 --> 00:07:51,907
[ Thinking ]
SHE SHOULD'VE LEFT ME

184
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:53,342
AFTER WHAT I DID.

185
00:07:53,408 --> 00:07:54,381
UH...
HEY!

186
00:07:54,381 --> 00:07:55,977
KENTA, I JUST WANT
TO TOUCH HIM!

187
00:07:55,977 --> 00:07:57,946
NUH-UH! YOU'RE JUST TRYING
TO FREAK HIM OUT!

188
00:07:57,979 --> 00:08:00,415
[ Thinking ]
I DON'T DESERVE TO BE HERE.

189
00:08:00,448 --> 00:08:03,051
DON'T THEY KNOW THAT?

190
00:08:03,051 --> 00:08:04,719
Rika: WOULD YOU CLOWNS
KNOCK IT OFF?

191
00:08:04,719 --> 00:08:08,156
Kazu: YOU CAN'T BOSS ME AROUND.
I AM A TAMER. NYAH!

192
00:08:10,225 --> 00:08:12,694
IT'S MOVING.
WHAT DO WE DO?

193
00:08:12,727 --> 00:08:15,363
THERE'S NOTHING WE CAN DO,
BUT WAIT

194
00:08:15,396 --> 00:08:17,866
AND HOPE IT DOESN'T
CHANGE ITS MIND AGAIN.

195
00:08:17,899 --> 00:08:19,734
Woman: THE ARK'S PROGRESS
HAS RESUMED.

196
00:08:19,734 --> 00:08:21,636
RECALCULATING
ROUTE COORDINATES.

197
00:08:21,669 --> 00:08:23,137
[ SHOUTING ]

198
00:08:23,171 --> 00:08:25,607
YOU CAN DO IT.
KEEP ON TRUCKING, ARK.

199
00:08:25,607 --> 00:08:26,808
JUST A LITTLE MORE.

200
00:08:26,841 --> 00:08:29,110
ALL THOSE KIDS
ARE DEPENDING ON YOU

201
00:08:29,110 --> 00:08:30,278
TO BRING THEM HOME.

202
00:08:30,278 --> 00:08:33,248
OH, NO, THE TRACK'S
OFF COURSE BY 12.4 DEGREES!

203
00:08:33,281 --> 00:08:35,283
HEY, NO SWEAT!
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

204
00:08:35,316 --> 00:08:38,253
LISTEN UP! SOMEONE HAS
TO TELL THE CHILDREN'S PARENTS

205
00:08:38,286 --> 00:08:40,255
THAT THE EMERGENCE POINT
HAS CHANGED.

206
00:08:40,288 --> 00:08:43,625
IT'S NOW IN THE MIDDLE
OF SHINJUKU PARK.

207
00:08:48,696 --> 00:08:50,632
Guilmon: THEN TAKATO'S DAD
SAID HE WOULD BAKE A BREAD

208
00:08:50,698 --> 00:08:51,695
THAT LOOKS JUST LIKE ME.

209
00:08:51,695 --> 00:08:53,487
I DON'T KNOW HOW
HE'S GOING TO DO THAT

210
00:08:53,487 --> 00:08:56,023
BECAUSE I DON'T LOOK ANYTHING
LIKE A LOAF OF BREAD.

211
00:08:56,089 --> 00:08:57,925
WELL, MAYBE WHEN I CURL UP
FOR A NAP.

212
00:08:57,958 --> 00:08:59,693
Takato: GUILMON, WHO ARE
YOU TALKING TO?

213
00:08:59,726 --> 00:09:01,395
THE ARK, SILLY.
WHAT -- THE ARK?

214
00:09:01,428 --> 00:09:03,697
WHY NOT? IT'S A REAL
GOOD LISTENER, TAKATO.

215
00:09:03,697 --> 00:09:05,833
I ASKED IT TO STOP
WHEN YOU COULDN'T GET ON,

216
00:09:05,866 --> 00:09:08,535
AND IT DID.
SO THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.

217
00:09:08,535 --> 00:09:11,572
WELL, IF YOU CAN HEAR ME,
THANK YOU, ARK.

218
00:09:11,638 --> 00:09:13,407
[ Thinking ]
IF IT WASN'T FOR YOU,

219
00:09:13,474 --> 00:09:15,576
WE'D BE DOING THE BACKSTROKE
IN THE SEA OF CHAOS BY NOW,

220
00:09:15,642 --> 00:09:19,346
INSTEAD OF GOING HOME.
HA HA.

221
00:09:19,379 --> 00:09:22,216
OH, JERI,
WE'LL GET YOU BACK.

222
00:09:22,216 --> 00:09:24,551
I PROMISE.

223
00:09:24,551 --> 00:09:28,455
Rika: DON'T WORRY, JERI.
WE'RE ALMOST HOME.

224
00:09:28,776 --> 00:09:30,899
OH.

225
00:09:30,899 --> 00:09:33,702
HANG IN THERE, OKAY?

226
00:09:33,735 --> 00:09:35,737
SO, TELL ME SOMETHING, RIKA.

227
00:09:35,771 --> 00:09:38,073
WHAT DO I GET FOR SAVING
YOUR LIFE NOT ONCE,

228
00:09:38,106 --> 00:09:39,508
BUT TWICE, HMM?

229
00:09:39,541 --> 00:09:41,209
HOW ABOUT
TWICE THE WHUPPIN'?

230
00:09:41,243 --> 00:09:42,711
YEAH, RIGHT. YOU WISH.

231
00:09:42,744 --> 00:09:44,913
[ LAUGHTER ]

232
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:47,415
[ BEEPING ]

233
00:09:47,482 --> 00:09:52,954
Kazu: WHY DO I GET THE FEELING
THIS ISN'T JUST TURBULENCE?

234
00:09:52,988 --> 00:09:54,723
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

235
00:09:54,790 --> 00:09:57,459
Guilmon: UM, IT LOOKS LIKE
THE LIGHT TRACK IS DISAPPEARING.

236
00:09:57,492 --> 00:09:59,227
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN,
TAKATO?

237
00:09:59,294 --> 00:10:03,799
HUH, WELL, I THINK IT MEANS
WE'RE IN TROUBLE!

238
00:10:08,036 --> 00:10:09,570
[ ALARM BLARING ]

239
00:10:09,570 --> 00:10:12,506
HUH? WHAT NOW?

240
00:10:12,573 --> 00:10:15,275
WE'RE HANGING IN THE MIDDLE
OF NOWHERE!

241
00:10:15,309 --> 00:10:17,411
WHAT ELSE COULD GO WRONG?

242
00:10:17,411 --> 00:10:20,414
UH, IT FEELS LIKE
WE'RE FALLING!

243
00:10:20,447 --> 00:10:23,751
I THINK THE ARK HAS LOST
ALL OF ITS STRENGTH!

244
00:10:23,751 --> 00:10:25,586
OH, MAN, WHEN THINGS
GO WRONG...

245
00:10:25,586 --> 00:10:27,121
WE'LL NEVER GET OUT
OF HERE!

246
00:10:27,187 --> 00:10:28,756
BUT WE WERE SO CLOSE.

247
00:10:28,789 --> 00:10:31,225
WITH THE TRACKS GONE,
THE ARK WON'T BE ABLE

248
00:10:31,258 --> 00:10:32,960
TO FIND ITS WAY BACK HOME.

249
00:10:33,027 --> 00:10:35,229
Takato: ARK,
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

250
00:10:35,262 --> 00:10:37,598
I KNOW YOU CAN HEAR ME.

251
00:10:37,665 --> 00:10:39,600
PLEASE, YOU'VE GOT
TO HELP US!

252
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:41,935
YOU'RE OUR ONLY CHANCE
OF GETTING OUT OF HERE!

253
00:10:42,002 --> 00:10:44,004
JUST A LITTLE FURTHER,
AND WE'LL BE HOME.

254
00:10:44,038 --> 00:10:45,806
OUR PARENTS ARE DEPENDING
ON YOU.

255
00:10:45,839 --> 00:10:47,374
PLEASE HELP US!

256
00:10:51,478 --> 00:10:54,448
HUH?

257
00:10:54,481 --> 00:10:55,983
THANKS.

258
00:10:55,983 --> 00:10:58,819
I TOLD YOU.
IT'S A REAL GOOD LISTENER.

259
00:10:58,852 --> 00:11:01,255
HUH?

260
00:11:06,694 --> 00:11:10,597
EVERYBODY, HOLD ON
TO SOMETHING!

261
00:11:10,664 --> 00:11:15,602
GUYS, THE ARK --
IT'S STARTING TO DISAPPEAR.

262
00:11:15,602 --> 00:11:18,138
Kazu: HEY, ARK, DUDE,
IF YOU GET US OUT OF THIS,

263
00:11:18,172 --> 00:11:20,341
I WILL HAND-WASH YOU
EVERY DAY OF THE WEEK,

264
00:11:20,374 --> 00:11:23,477
VACUUM YOUR INSIDES,
YOU NAME IT!

265
00:11:23,510 --> 00:11:25,846
Kenta: MARINEANGEMON,
I'LL MISS YOU!

266
00:11:25,879 --> 00:11:27,981
[ Thinking ]
COME ON, ARK, YOU CAN DO IT!

267
00:11:27,981 --> 00:11:29,717
I KNOW YOU CAN.

268
00:11:38,992 --> 00:11:44,164
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

269
00:11:49,269 --> 00:11:51,705
THAT'S NORMAL, RIGHT?

270
00:11:51,705 --> 00:11:54,375
THAT DEPENDS ON HOW
YOU DEFINE "NORMAL," JANYUU.

271
00:12:29,710 --> 00:12:31,879
AHH...

272
00:12:34,202 --> 00:12:37,839
HA HA HA HA!

273
00:12:41,843 --> 00:12:43,678
[ GIGGLES ]

274
00:13:11,339 --> 00:13:14,008
[ Thinking ]
BACK HOME, WHERE I DON'T BELONG.

275
00:13:15,877 --> 00:13:18,379
HUH? IMPMON...

276
00:13:20,381 --> 00:13:22,183
Riley: I JUST FOUND
JERI'S PARENTS.

277
00:13:22,183 --> 00:13:24,419
THEY'RE STAYING WITH RELATIVES
IN EAST MATSUMOTO.

278
00:13:24,452 --> 00:13:26,254
Yamaki: SO, WHEN WILL THEY
BE HERE?

279
00:13:26,287 --> 00:13:28,022
THAT'S THE THING --
THEY WON'T.

280
00:13:28,089 --> 00:13:29,257
HUH?

281
00:13:29,290 --> 00:13:31,759
YOU SEE, HER FATHER
SAID SHE LEFT

282
00:13:31,793 --> 00:13:35,230
ON HER OWN, SO SHE CAN
COME BACK ON HER OWN.

283
00:13:35,230 --> 00:13:37,065
WE COULD SEND ONE
OF OUR OPERATIVES

284
00:13:37,098 --> 00:13:40,235
TO TAKE HER THERE,
BUT TO BE ALONE...

285
00:13:40,268 --> 00:13:43,872
THE POOR THING.

286
00:13:43,905 --> 00:13:46,908
WAIT! I'LL TAKE HER HOME!

287
00:13:46,908 --> 00:13:47,909
HUH?

288
00:13:47,942 --> 00:13:49,410
LISTEN TO ME!

289
00:13:49,444 --> 00:13:50,912
JERI'S ALL BY HERSELF.

290
00:13:50,945 --> 00:13:53,246
SHE NEEDS TO BE WITH SOMEONE
SHE KNOWS RIGHT NOW.

291
00:13:53,246 --> 00:13:55,539
BUT, TAKATO,
THAT'S SO FAR AWAY.

292
00:13:55,539 --> 00:13:57,374
HONEY, LET HIM GO.
REALLY?

293
00:13:57,374 --> 00:13:58,776
Guilmon: REALLY?

294
00:13:58,809 --> 00:14:01,278
WELL, IT'S NOT LIKE WE WON'T
KNOW WHERE YOU ARE THIS TIME.

295
00:14:01,311 --> 00:14:04,114
BESIDES, WE TRUST YOU.

296
00:14:04,181 --> 00:14:06,216
MY LITTLE BOY
IS ALL GROWN UP.

297
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,518
[ GIGGLES ]

298
00:14:07,551 --> 00:14:09,720
NOW, REMEMBER, TAKATO,
AS SOON AS YOU'VE GOTTEN

299
00:14:09,753 --> 00:14:11,889
JERI HOME SAFELY, GO STRAIGHT
TO YOUR AUNT'S HOUSE.

300
00:14:11,922 --> 00:14:13,524
WE'LL BE WAITING FOR YOU.

301
00:14:13,524 --> 00:14:15,392
IS THAT OKAY?

302
00:14:15,425 --> 00:14:17,361
MM-HMM. YEAH, MOM.
THANKS.

303
00:14:19,696 --> 00:14:21,031
ALL RIGHT THEN.

304
00:14:21,031 --> 00:14:23,033
THE STREETS OUT OF SHINJUKU
ARE CLOSED OFF,

305
00:14:23,066 --> 00:14:24,902
SO YOU'LL HAVE TO TAKE
A TRAIN.

306
00:14:24,968 --> 00:14:26,703
[ RUMBLING ]

307
00:14:26,737 --> 00:14:30,307
Dolphin: OH, NO, THE ARK --
IT'S DISINTEGRATING!

308
00:14:32,142 --> 00:14:33,977
MY BABY!

309
00:14:38,596 --> 00:14:41,065
GOODBYE, ARK!

310
00:14:43,015 --> 00:14:46,619
GOODBYE, ARK...
AND THANK YOU.

311
00:14:52,158 --> 00:14:54,760
Guilmon: [ Sighs ] I FEEL
LIKE I'VE LOST A FRIEND.

312
00:14:54,794 --> 00:14:56,295
Takato: ME TOO, BOY.

313
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:05,644
OH...

314
00:15:05,644 --> 00:15:09,214
TIME TO GO, BUT NO TAKATO!
WHY DOES THIS KEEP HAPPENING?

315
00:15:09,281 --> 00:15:10,782
Takato: HOLD ON,
COMING THROUGH!

316
00:15:10,816 --> 00:15:13,752
I WAS WORRIED. IT WAS LIKE
THE ARK ALL OVER AGAIN,

317
00:15:13,785 --> 00:15:15,787
EXCEPT I CAN'T TELL
THE TRAIN TO STOP.

318
00:15:15,821 --> 00:15:17,756
THERE'S NO NEED TO.

319
00:15:17,789 --> 00:15:20,225
WHO'S THE EXTRA
LUNCH BOX FOR?
GUILMON...

320
00:15:20,259 --> 00:15:22,261
JUST ASKING.

321
00:15:22,294 --> 00:15:24,963
UH, HEY, JERI.

322
00:15:28,628 --> 00:15:31,063
Porter: MONSTER ONBOARD!

323
00:15:31,063 --> 00:15:32,966
AAH! STAY BACK!
I KNOW JUJITSU!

324
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:34,467
WAIT, IT'S OKAY!
I PAID FOR HIM.

325
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,970
I KNOW HE'S KIND OF BIG,
SO I GOT HIM AN ADULT TICKET.

326
00:15:36,970 --> 00:15:39,472
WHO CARES ABOUT THE TICKET?
THAT THING'S A DIGIMON, RIGHT?

327
00:15:39,472 --> 00:15:40,940
AND DIGIMON ARE DANGEROUS!

328
00:15:40,974 --> 00:15:42,976
THAT MONSTER
SHOULD BE IN A CAGE.

329
00:15:43,042 --> 00:15:45,778
YOU TAKE THAT BACK!
HE'S A GOOD DIGIMON,

330
00:15:45,845 --> 00:15:48,548
AND DON'T CALL HIM A MONSTER.
HE'S VERY SENSITIVE.

331
00:15:48,581 --> 00:15:50,016
YEAH.

332
00:15:50,049 --> 00:15:52,218
HA! WHAT DO YOU THINK I AM,
DUMB OR SOMETHING?

333
00:15:52,252 --> 00:15:53,820
NO.

334
00:15:53,853 --> 00:15:56,522
HMM, THAT THING IS
A NATURAL BORN MENACE.

335
00:15:56,556 --> 00:15:58,725
GUILMON'S JUST A BABY.
HE COULDN'T HURT A FLY.

336
00:15:58,758 --> 00:16:00,960
Guilmon: I'M NOT A BABY.
I'LL SHOW YOU.

337
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,762
GUILMON, DIGIVOLVE!

338
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:04,931
AAH!

339
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:06,833
GUILMON, CUT IT OUT.
THIS ISN'T HELPING.

340
00:16:06,899 --> 00:16:09,302
BUT I'M NOT A BABY!
LET ME SHOW HIM!

341
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:11,938
I TOLD YOU,
HE'S A MENACE TO SOCIETY!

342
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:13,973
[ STOMACH GURGLING ]

343
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:17,844
HUNGRY. I JUST WANT
MY LUNCH BOX.

344
00:16:17,844 --> 00:16:19,345
HMM...

345
00:16:19,379 --> 00:16:21,381
[ STOMACH GURGLING ]

346
00:16:21,414 --> 00:16:23,016
HA HA HA HA.

347
00:16:23,016 --> 00:16:25,985
HEY, I NEVER HEARD OF A MONSTER
WANTING A LUNCH BOX.

348
00:16:26,019 --> 00:16:27,553
YOUR FRIEND'S PRETTY FUNNY.

349
00:16:27,587 --> 00:16:30,490
YEAH, THAT'S GUILMON.
HE'S A RIOT.

350
00:16:30,523 --> 00:16:32,492
HE REMINDS ME
OF MY KID BROTHER...

351
00:16:32,525 --> 00:16:34,694
UH, EXCEPT FOR THE CLAWS,
OF COURSE. HERE YOU GO.

352
00:16:34,727 --> 00:16:36,362
GEE, THANKS, MISTER.

353
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:38,398
I'LL JUST PRETEND
I DIDN'T SEE HIM, OKAY?

354
00:16:38,464 --> 00:16:39,866
YEAH, OKAY.

355
00:16:39,866 --> 00:16:42,602
BYE NOW.
HUH, CRAZY KIDS.

356
00:16:42,635 --> 00:16:45,038
Takato: OH...
THAT WAS CLOSE.

357
00:16:45,038 --> 00:16:47,507
GUILMON, WHY'D YOU TRY
TO DIGIVOLVE?

358
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:50,576
I DON'T KNOW. I CAN'T THINK
WHEN I'M HUNGRY.

359
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:52,957
I'M STILL HUNGRY...

360
00:16:52,957 --> 00:16:56,127
BUT TOO SLEEPY TO EAT...

361
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,595
HUH? UH...

362
00:16:59,628 --> 00:17:01,196
UM, JERI?

363
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:03,532
YOU HAVEN'T EATEN
ANYTHING.

364
00:17:03,565 --> 00:17:06,068
AREN'T YOU HUNGRY?

365
00:17:06,068 --> 00:17:07,903
WELL, GUESS NOT.

366
00:17:07,903 --> 00:17:11,573
YOU KNOW, JERI, I'VE ALWAYS
WANTED TO TELL YOU,

367
00:17:11,573 --> 00:17:13,709
YOU'RE THE NICEST GIRL
I'VE EVER MET.

368
00:17:13,742 --> 00:17:16,712
I THINK...

369
00:17:16,745 --> 00:17:19,081
I MEAN, YOU ALWAYS TALKED
TO ME AND STUFF

370
00:17:19,147 --> 00:17:21,583
WHEN NO ONE ELSE WOULD,
AND IT MAY SOUND SILLY,

371
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:24,786
BUT SOMETIMES, I IMAGINED THAT
YOU MIGHT KIND OF LIKE ME

372
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:28,123
THE WAY THAT I LIKE YOU.

373
00:17:28,156 --> 00:17:31,059
WELL, I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE
I THINK ABOUT YOU ALL THE TIME,

374
00:17:31,126 --> 00:17:32,594
'CAUSE I DO!

375
00:17:32,628 --> 00:17:34,963
UH, THIS IS HARD.
WHAT I'M TRYING TO SAY,

376
00:17:34,997 --> 00:17:37,466
MORE THAN JUST
A FRIEND, JERI,

377
00:17:37,466 --> 00:17:40,168
IS THAT I LIKE YOU.

378
00:17:40,202 --> 00:17:41,803
I REALLY DO.

379
00:17:46,808 --> 00:17:49,311
I HATE SEEING YOU
THIS WAY.

380
00:17:49,378 --> 00:17:52,981
WHEN THIS WHOLE THING
STARTED,

381
00:17:53,048 --> 00:17:54,783
I WAS SO HAPPY,

382
00:17:54,816 --> 00:17:56,818
'CAUSE YOU WERE A TAMER
AND GOT TO COME

383
00:17:56,885 --> 00:17:59,221
TO THE DIGITAL WORLD
WITH US.

384
00:17:59,254 --> 00:18:03,625
THEN LEOMON DIED...

385
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:05,627
AND YOU BECAME SO SAD.

386
00:18:05,627 --> 00:18:08,130
I THOUGHT IF I BROUGHT YOU
BACK HOME TO THE REAL WORLD,

387
00:18:08,163 --> 00:18:10,265
MAYBE YOU'D BE YOURSELF
AGAIN.

388
00:18:10,299 --> 00:18:12,801
BUT NOW YOU JUST SIT HERE
NOT SAYING OR DOING ANYTHING.

389
00:18:12,801 --> 00:18:15,137
I KEEP THINKING, HOW MUCH
OF THIS IS MY FAULT?

390
00:18:15,170 --> 00:18:17,172
THAT IF I NEVER BROUGHT YOU
TO THE DIGITAL WORLD,

391
00:18:17,239 --> 00:18:18,640
YOU'D STILL BE HAPPY.

392
00:18:18,674 --> 00:18:21,276
BUT YOU'RE NOT.

393
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:24,146
I'M SO SORRY, JERI.

394
00:18:24,212 --> 00:18:26,548
I'M SORRY YOU HAD
TO GO THROUGH ALL THAT,

395
00:18:26,582 --> 00:18:28,617
THAT I COULDN'T HELP
SAVE LEOMON.

396
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:32,554
I JUST WISH YOU WOULD TALK
TO ME, JERI!

397
00:18:32,587 --> 00:18:36,124
[ SOBBING ]

398
00:18:36,191 --> 00:18:37,609
[ SIGHS ]

399
00:18:37,609 --> 00:18:40,027
PROTEIN --
26.4 GRAMS...

400
00:18:40,027 --> 00:18:44,331
SATURATED FAT --
15.7 GRAMS...

401
00:18:44,365 --> 00:18:47,575
CARBOHYDRATES --
102.2 GRAMS.

402
00:18:47,575 --> 00:18:49,544
SODIUM --
4.6 GRAMS...

403
00:18:49,577 --> 00:18:51,546
JERI?

404
00:18:51,579 --> 00:18:56,551
[ WHISTLE BLOWING ]

405
00:18:56,584 --> 00:18:58,319
WAKE UP, GUILMON.
WE'RE HERE.

406
00:18:58,353 --> 00:18:59,821
WHERE'S HERE?

407
00:18:59,854 --> 00:19:02,023
WATCH YOUR STEP, JERI.

408
00:19:02,090 --> 00:19:03,892
THAT'S IT.

409
00:19:03,925 --> 00:19:06,227
LOOK, THERE'S YOUR DAD.

410
00:19:09,230 --> 00:19:11,733
[ GRUNTS ]

411
00:19:11,766 --> 00:19:15,070
HELLO, MR. KATOU.

412
00:19:16,971 --> 00:19:20,075
THANK YOU
FOR BRINGING HER BACK HOME.

413
00:19:20,108 --> 00:19:22,043
UM, YOU'RE WELCOME.

414
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:24,012
COME ON, YOUNG LADY.

415
00:19:25,662 --> 00:19:27,705
BYE, JERI.

416
00:19:27,705 --> 00:19:29,540
GOODBYE.

417
00:19:32,543 --> 00:19:35,279
COME ON, BUDDY,
LET'S GO.

418
00:19:35,312 --> 00:19:36,714
Man on TV: THIS JUST IN...

419
00:19:36,781 --> 00:19:38,582
THERE ARE REPORTS
OF STRANGE SIGHTINGS

420
00:19:38,582 --> 00:19:39,917
AROUND THE EVACUATED
SHINJUKU AREA.

421
00:19:39,950 --> 00:19:41,585
IN RECENT WEEKS,
SHINJUKU HAS SUSTAINED...

422
00:19:53,431 --> 00:19:55,933
JERI!

423
00:19:59,937 --> 00:20:01,439
HUH?

424
00:20:01,439 --> 00:20:02,940
I'VE BEEN SO WORRIED
ABOUT YOU,

425
00:20:03,007 --> 00:20:05,242
BUT YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

426
00:20:05,276 --> 00:20:07,278
Man on TV: WE HAVE JUST
RECEIVED FOOTAGE

427
00:20:07,278 --> 00:20:09,580
OF THE STRANGE APPARITIONS
IN THE SHINJUKU AREA.

428
00:20:09,613 --> 00:20:11,649
GREAT QUANTITIES
OF A RED FORMLESS MATTER

429
00:20:11,682 --> 00:20:13,938
APPEAR TO BE ENGULFING
THE CITY.

430
00:20:13,938 --> 00:20:15,873
EYEWITNESSES SAY THE SUBSTANCE

431
00:20:15,873 --> 00:20:17,809
IS INCREASING
AT AN ALARMING RATE.

432
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:19,911
THIS CAN'T BE HAPPENING.

433
00:20:19,944 --> 00:20:22,046
WHAT'S GOING ON, TAKATO?

434
00:20:22,046 --> 00:20:26,551
THE CHAOS --
IT FOLLOWED US HOME!

435
00:20:26,551 --> 00:20:30,588
WHOA, THAT'S A SOUVENIR
YOU DON'T WANT!

436
00:20:30,655 --> 00:20:32,723
WHAT ARE THE TAMERS GOING
TO DO NOW?

437
00:20:32,723 --> 00:20:36,127
FIND OUT ON THE NEXT
"DIGIMON -- DIGITAL MONSTERS."

